cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a quantized decoding algorithm for LDPC codes based on an information-theoretic criterion. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The proposed algorithm can be applied to improve the error correction performance of communication systems that use LDPC codes. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes different decoder design parameters and complexity reduction techniques to improve the performance of the proposed algorithm. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a look-up table (LUT) based algorithm for LDPC decoding, which involves designing an efficient data structure for the LUT. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The proposed algorithm can be applied to improve the error correction performance of multimedia communication systems that use LDPC codes.
